SVN2FTP
=======

-------------
Configuration
-------------
Copy the sample.ini and adjust it to your needs.

-------------
Usage Windows
-------------
cd C:\Path\to\svn2ftp\bin
svn2ftp -c C:\Path\To\Project.ini -r 175:HEAD
svn2ftp -c C:\Path\To\Project.ini -r 163

If you did not add the PHP directory to you PATH
environment variable, you must use "php svn2ftp.php"
instead of "svn2ftp".

Tip: If you add the "bin" directory to your PATH
     environment variable you're able to use
     "svn2ftp" without switching to the SVN2FTP
     "bin" directory. :]

-----------
Usage Linux
-----------
cd /path/to/svn2ftp/bin
php svn2ftp.php -c /path/to/project.ini -r 175:HEAD
php svn2ftp.php -c /path/to/project.ini -r 163
